 536}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10090"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "murine", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.8528796434402466, "span": {"begin": 510, "end": 516}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7124"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TNF&alpha;", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9726713299751282, "span": {"begin": 568, "end": 578}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3552"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-1&alpha;", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9705278277397156, "span": {"begin": 583, "end": 594}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7124"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TNF&alpha;", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9730799794197083, "span": {"begin": 780, "end": 790}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3552"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-1&alpha;", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9812889099121094, "span": {"begin": 795, "end": 806}}], "text": "In the study of Murphy et al, the human monocytic THP-1 cells treated with carbon nanotubes (CNTs) that induce frustrated phagocytosis showed an increase production of IL-1&beta;, IL-6 and IL-8 whereas treatment by CNTs that did not induce this process did not induce production of these cytokines [2]. Similarly, it was shown that exposure to fibres that induced frustrated phagocytosis of primary human alveolar macrophages is accompanied by induction of IL-6 and IL-8 [3], and exposure of immortalized MH-S murine alveolar macrophage is accompanied by induction of TNF&alpha; and IL-1&alpha; [4, 5]. The induction of cytokines was observed in lesser extend after cell treatment with fibres that did not cause frustrated phagocytosis. Indeed, the ratio of the dose-response for TNF&alpha; and IL-1&alpha; of long fibres to short fibres was about 11 [4, 5].", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:20:54 +0000 2026"}